      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The final of the words denoting ' many '</l>
<l>may be lenghtened in some compounds in poetry.<note place="foot">E.g. instead of<foreign xml:lang="ta">palacila</foreign> one may have <foreign xml:lang="ta">palāañcilāa pulavar ;</foreign> the <foreign xml:lang="ta">pala cila</foreign>
          is considered a <foreign xml:lang="ta">cevveṇ,</foreign> i.e. enumeration of series of
          items with the conjunctive particle ' under-stood '. It seems that <foreign xml:lang="ta">ceyyuḷ</foreign> ' poetry ' has preserved here some older forms (<foreign xml:lang="ta">palām, cilām).</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
